    <h1>United boss re&#xAD;tains Maguire as skip&#xAD;per</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200913/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-13"><time>2020-09-13</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Ole Gun­nar Sol­sk­jaer yes­ter­day con­firmed Harry Maguire will re­main Manch­ester United’s cap­tain this sea­son de­spite his in­volve­ment in a Greek court case.</p>
    <p>The Eng­land de­fender was given a 21-month sus­pended sen­tence last month af­ter he was found guilty of as­sault­ing a po­lice of­fi­cer, swear­ing, re­sist­ing ar­rest and bribery dur­ing an in­ci­dent on the re­sort is­land of Mykonos.</p>
    <p>The 27-year-old has de­nied the of­fences and has since launched an ap­peal, which is ex­pected to be heard later this month, and Sol­sk­jaer has thrown his sup­port be­hind the player, telling MUTV he was “an ab­so­lute top hu­man be­ing”.</p>


